  "prompt": "What's the meaning of ISO?",
  "response": "ISO can refer to multiple meanings depending on the context. Here are a few common interpretations:\n\n1. **International Organization for Standardization**: This is perhaps the most widely recognized usage. ISO is an independent, non-governmental international organization that develops and publishes standards for a wide range of industries, ensuring quality, safety, efficiency, and interoperability of products and services.\n\n2. **ISO (Image File)**: In computing, an ISO file is an archive file of an optical disc's file system. It is commonly used to distribute large software packages, operating system installation images, or backup media.\n\n3. **ISO Sensitivity (Photography)**: In photography, ISO refers to the sensitivity of a camera's sensor to light. Higher ISO settings allow for better performance in low light conditions but can introduce more noise in the image.\n\n4. **Isometric (in Mathematics/Games)**: In geometry or game design, \"iso\" might refer to isometric projection, a method for visually representing three-dimensional objects in two dimensions.\n\nThe specific meaning of ISO will depend on the field in which it is being used.",
